article.headline: Texas-Pan American 63, South Dakota St. 50
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas (AP) -- Paul Stroll and Dexter Shankle scored 14 points apiece to lead Texas-Pan American to a 63-50 win over South Dakota State on Thursday night. Brian Burrell and Colin Lien added 11 each for the Broncs (13-11). South Dakota State was led by Jose Frias, who scored 12 points. Garrett Callahan and Casey Mackenzie had 11 apiece. The Jackrabbits (5-20) were plagued by poor shooting, particularly from behind the 3-point line, where they were 1-for-14. The Broncs led 29-19 at halftime.
